div1.p: United States District Court WESYERM DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON HABEAS CORPUS
The President of the UNited States of America To King Dykeman, Seattle Washingon,

Greetig: We Command you, that you have the body of Mrs. Gladys Fredrika Fuson by you imprisoned and detained, as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonement and detetion, by whatsoever name said Mrs. Gladys Frefika Fuson shall be called or charged befire the Hon. G.L. Hanford, Edward B. Cushman United States District Judge for the Westerm District of Washington, at Court ROom in the City of Seattle in the Northern Division of said District of Washington, on the 27th day of October, 1916, A.D 189000, at two o'clock in the after noon, to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning - - - - - the said Mrs. Gladys Fredika Fuson. And have you then and here this writ.

WITNESS the Hon.G.L. HANFORD, Edward E. Cushman, Judge of the United States District Court for the Western District of Wshington, this 26th day of October in the year of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and nine hundred sixteen.
